## 7. Mirror Resonance

TERA also studies whether a vector remains coherent under reflection.

Let \(M\) be a mirror operator.
Then mirror resonance can be written as

\[
R_s(t)=\cos\angle(\mathbf{v}(t),M(\mathbf{v}(t)))
\]

Interpretation:

- \(R_s(t)\approx 1\): strong reflective coherence
- \(R_s(t)\approx 0\): weak readable return
- \(R_s(t)<0\): inversion, distortion, or break

Mirror resonance asks whether a system becomes clearer when reflected back through another structure.

